Description: administration and health-check tool for the DSMR mail stack
 dsmr-email-admin is a command-line tool for operators of the DSMR
 qmail/vpopmail/dovecot mail stack.  It generalises the recurring
 verification-and-repair steps a stack accumulates when a control or
 configuration file predates a packaging fix: a postinst that only creates
 a file "if absent" never repairs an existing one on upgrade.
 .
 The 'check' subcommand runs a read-only health check across packages,
 services, the PostgreSQL backend, dovecot authentication, the qmail-smtpd
 softlimit, relay rules, and listening ports.
 .
 The 'fix' subcommand repairs the known stale-config faults, each behind a
 detector so nothing the admin set deliberately is overwritten:
   - a qmail softlimit too low for the OpenSSL/krb5 library footprint
     (which makes qmail-smtpd fail to start);
   - vpopmail.pgsql with its password and database fields swapped;
   - a dovecot SQL connection file out of sync with vpopmail.pgsql;
   - a stopped or unenabled vpopmail PostgreSQL cluster.
 .
 The 'selftest' subcommand proves delivery and dovecot authentication end to
 end using a throwaway vpopmail mailbox that it then removes.  Every fix backs
 up the file it changes before writing.
